# Environment variables live with the app/worker that needs them, each
# documented in its own .env.example. Copy the relevant one to .env.local
# (frontends) or .dev.vars (the api worker) and fill in values. .env.local
# and .dev.vars are gitignored. Never commit real secrets.
# See specs/06-secrets-policy.md for the full policy.
#
# Where to look:
#   apps/live/.env.example       NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE, Clerk publishable key, telemetry toggle
#   apps/telemetry/.env.example  NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE
#   apps/api/.env.example        Clerk JWKS, guest-id HMAC, OpenAI, image caps, telemetry (Worker vars/secrets)
#
# The repo root itself needs no env vars.
